Aaron Hernandez is on trial for the murder of semi-pro football player Odin Lloyd in June 2013 . 
  His defense argued that he saw his friends kill Lloyd but did not commit the murder himself . 
  The jury began deliberations on Tuesday afternoon . 
  The former New England Patriots football player has pleaded not guilty to murder and firearms charges in the death of Lloyd . 
  Prosecutors say he and two friends killed Lloyd near his home in Boston . 
  Hernandez and Lloyd shared the same DNA at the scene of the murder . 
  The defense said Carlos Ortiz and Ernest Wallace were responsible for the killing . 
 